summary: An ordinance amending Section 2 of Ordinance No. 33355, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the manner of advertising and receiving bids for bonds of the City of Seattle in the sum of Four Hundred Four Thousand ($404,000) Dollars of bonds from an issue of Four Hundred Twenty-five Thousand ($425,000) Dollars of bonds voted at an election held in said city, March 4, 1913, under and pursuant to Ordinance No. 30328, and canceling the remainder of said proposed issue", approved July 9, 1914.
